{"cursor":"7772","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Multidrug tolerance' or 'antibiotic tolerance' is the ability of a disease-\ncausing microorganism to resist killing by antibiotics or other antimicrobials.\nIt is mechanistically distinct from multidrug resistance: It is not caused by mutant microbes, but rather by\nmicrobial cells that exist in a transient, dormant, non-dividing state.\nMicroorganisms that display multidrug tolerance can be bacteria, fungi or\nparasites.\n","linknr":231,"url":"Multidrug_tolerance","recorded":1362538118,"links":14,"instances":["medicine"],"pdf":["http://www.phys.huji.ac.il/bio_physics/nathalie/GefenFEMS2009.pdf","http://www.phys.huji.ac.il/bio_physics/nathalie/GefenFEMS2009.pdf","http://www.ias.ac.in/jbiosci/dec2008/795.pdf","http://www.ias.ac.in/jbiosci/dec2008/795.pdf"],"categories":["Antibiotics","Bacteria","Infectious disease"],"headings":["Relevance to chronic infections","Medical importance","Distinction from multidrug resistance","Molecular mechanisms","Potential treatment","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["implant","medicine"]],"members":["implant"],"related":["Microorganism","Antibiotic","Antimicrobial","Mutant","Dormancy","Bacteria","Pathogenic_fungi","Protozoa","Infection","Biofilm","Implant_(medicine)","Catheter","Urinary_tract_infection","Otitis_media","Cystic_fibrosis","Phenotype","Antibiotic_resistance","Horizontal_gene_transfer","Heredity","Offspring","Antibiotic_sensitivity","Stochastic","Nature.com","Aminoglycosides","Proton","Nature.com","Antibiotic_resistance","Antibiotic_sensitivity","Bacteria","Biofilm","Chronic_wound","Dormancy","Infection","Infectious_Disease","Multidrug_resistance","Pathogen","Relapse"]}